    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1585"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1585">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/70.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">German Embassy</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">memorandum</hi>.</p>
                <p>Referring to the Imperial German Embassy’s memorandum of the 1st instant, seeking
                    the good offices of the Government of the United States to the end that proper
                    protection may be accorded to the lives and property of German subjects in the
                    vicinity of Guadalajara, Mexico, the Department of State has the honor to inform
                    the Imperial German Embassy that, in compliance with the request of the
                    Department of State made to the Secretary of the Navy that Admiral Howard be
                    instructed to lend his good offices looking to the protection of German subjects
                    along the west coast of Mexico, the Secretary of the Navy, on June 1 last, sent
                    telegraphic instructions in the above sense to the Commander-in-Chief of the
                    Atlantic [Pacific] Fleet, with special reference to the expected attack upon
                    Guadalajara by Constitutionalists.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 10, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
